				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: AE Kiting: Getting that circle started<a name="48770"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 28 04 2:18 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">This is how I usually start it: 
<br />

<br />
1) Do what Shass says and group them into a circle by running a few manual circles, keep a good distance, no heroics here. 
<br />

<br />
2) After they are all nicely stacked, make a tight circle, not quite close enough to get hit but close enough to see their blood shot eyes, if you know what I mean. 
<br />

<br />
3) This is the tricky part, as soon as you come out of your VERY tight circle tap enter twice(when you do this you should already be holding down forward + left/right, if not be sure you are) 
<br />

<br />
4) You will notice yourself drift straight for half a second then turn into the circle with the mobs very close to you, then you get your autocircle. 
<br />

<br />
I'd suggest practicing on 1 or 2 mobs to start. Trial and error sucks when you get continuously beat down by 30 mobs.</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
Quoted myself from a post I made a while back regarding starting up the kite. Its not very hard, I rarely ever make mistakes starting the kite. But if no matter what you can't seem to do it, mem kazumis and use it during the period of time you are trying to start your kite.
<br />

<br />
EDIT: Kazumis would be only an option after you reach 60, of course. <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-10.gif" border="0" alt="Blushing" hspace="2" /></span></td>
