				<td colspan="2"><span>What i've found that works for me is running a manual circle a few times to bunch them. Now heres the scarey part. Run off a ways, turn around and run almost directly AT them....  run maybe 5degrees off them..(basically aim to pass them around the same distance as when you're kiting them.  As soon as you are directly beside them take a sharp left and do the enter thingie. Almost 95% of the time i dont get hit.    Sounds insane and definately looks it, but it works for me.
<br />

<br />
I use LoH and BDMG to kite, for stings and percussion. I dont bother with switching instruments. </span></td>
