				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: AE Kiting: Getting that circle started<a name="49082"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 29 04 3:05 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Lately what I've been doing is setting up the circle with a drum that's way too fast to get a good circle, like Selo's (or TDoK once I've bought my white scale and saved up enough cash for one), your circle is huge so it's easy to set it up where they won't hit you, but your AE won't hit them either.  Then, slowly switch drums until they get range of your low radius AE.  I carry a bunch of drums on me when I AE kite now.  Selo's, store bought Hand Drum, etc.
<br />

<br />
I think I just needed more practice when I asked the question, it's much better now :p.
<br />

